php server
    Definition:
      - When we run php we have to run php on a web server
      - This means php is a server-side languages, in order to interact with our websites
      - server comes with php
    
    Create a web server:
      - We can run in our console:
        ❯ php -S localhost:4000
        This will create a little web server for us in order to run our php files

    Execution step:
      - Whenever we refresh our page(localhost:4000), the web server will execute 
        the php code in sequence!

-- console 
❯ php -S localhost:4000
[Fri Nov 18 11:17:10 2022] PHP 8.1.12 Development Server (http://localhost:4000) started

